 {"id":"franken_numpy-jv28","title":"Extend G7 sentinel workloads to broader op-family coverage","description":"## Why this exists\n\nCommit 27f27f2 (2026-04-08) added memory/allocation/fragmentation SLOs to the G7 performance budget gate — a real expansion of what gets gated. But the underlying sentinel workload set has not been audited for breadth in this expansion. The reality check found that G7's workloads cluster around ufunc and axis-reduction hot paths (the \"~56% reduction in axis-reduction latency\" mentioned in README L928), with thinner coverage of linalg, fft, random, and io — exactly the op-families most likely to surprise users when they migrate from NumPy.\n\n## Background / context for future-self\n\n- G7 is run by scripts/e2e/run_performance_budget_gate.sh (3.7 KB, recently updated).\n- The performance budget gate binary is crates/fnp-conformance/src/bin/run_performance_budget_gate.rs.\n- The existing benchmark baseline lives at artifacts/baselines/ufunc_benchmark_baseline.json.\n- The G7 gate measures p50/p95/p99 latency for sentinel workloads and rejects regressions that exceed a configured threshold (SLO).\n- Recent work (27f27f2) added memory/allocation/fragmentation SLOs alongside latency SLOs.\n- After franken_numpy-azql produces the cross-engine benchmark, we'll know which op-families have the LARGEST performance gap vs NumPy. Those are the families where a regression gate is most valuable — we don't want to accidentally make a bad gap worse.\n\n## Goals\n\n1. **Audit current sentinel coverage:** Read the existing G7 workload configuration and produce a coverage matrix:\n   - **Rows:** op-families (ufunc-elementwise, ufunc-broadcast, reductions-contiguous, reductions-strided, sort, matmul, linalg-decomposition, linalg-solve, fft, random-continuous, random-discrete, npy-io, text-io).\n   - **Columns:** (workload count, latency SLO present, memory SLO present, allocation SLO present).\n   - Highlight cells with zero coverage (these are the blind spots).\n\n2. **Design new sentinels for uncovered families:** For each zero-coverage cell, design at least 2 sentinel workloads that:\n   - Exercise the hot path (not edge cases — those are for correctness tests, not perf gates).\n   - Use realistic array sizes (medium tier: ~10K elements for array ops, ~100x100 for linalg, ~4096 for fft).\n   - Have stable, deterministic inputs (no RNG in the benchmark setup — use fixed seeds).\n   - Target: expand from current count to at least 2 workloads per op-family.\n\n3. **Align with cross-engine findings:** After azql closes, cross-reference the cross-engine benchmark results. If an op-family shows ratio > 5x vs NumPy, ensure it has at least 3 sentinels (not 2) in G7 — we need tighter regression monitoring where the gap is already large.\n\n4. **Backward-compatible baseline extension:** The new sentinels must be ADDED to the existing baseline JSON schema, not replacing it. The G7 gate must continue to validate the old sentinels AND the new ones. Schema evolution approach:\n   - Add a `\"schema_version\": \"2.0\"` field to the baseline JSON.\n   - The gate script accepts both v1 (old sentinels only) and v2 (old + new) baselines.\n   - First run with v2 generates the new baseline; subsequent runs gate against it.\n\n5. **Re-baseline and emit delta artifact:** Run the full sentinel set, capture the new baseline, and emit a delta artifact (`artifacts/baselines/ufunc_benchmark_baseline_delta_v2.json`) comparing old vs new coverage counts.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Blocked by franken_numpy-azql (cross-engine benchmark) so new sentinels can be aligned with worst-ratio op-families.\n\n## Unit test requirements\n\nTests MUST be inline #[cfg(test)] in the relevant conformance source files:\n\n1. **Coverage matrix generation:** Given a mock workload config with 3 families (2 covered, 1 empty), verify the matrix correctly identifies the zero-coverage cell.\n2. **Sentinel validation:** Verify new sentinel WorkloadSpec entries have all required fields (family, name, input_shape, expected_dtype, SLO thresholds).\n3. **Schema version migration:** Verify that a v1 baseline JSON can be loaded and extended with v2 sentinels without data loss. Verify a v2 baseline rejects missing fields from new sentinels.\n4. **Deterministic input generation:** Verify that sentinel inputs generated from fixed seeds produce identical arrays across runs (byte-exact comparison).\n5. **SLO threshold bounds:** Verify that SLO thresholds are positive, non-zero, and within a sane range (no accidentally-set thresholds of 0ns or 1 year).\n\n## E2E test requirements\n\nAfter implementation, `scripts/e2e/run_performance_budget_gate.sh` must:\n- Run with the expanded sentinel set and pass (no regression since we just baselined).\n- Log which sentinels are new vs existing.\n- Support `--coverage-report` flag that prints the coverage matrix to stdout for manual inspection.\n- The delta artifact must exist and be valid JSON.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Coverage matrix produced showing all 13 op-families with current sentinel counts.\n- [ ] Zero-coverage families each have at least 2 new sentinel workloads.\n- [ ] Sentinels aligned with azql results (op-families with ratio > 5x get 3+ sentinels).\n- [ ] Baseline JSON schema extended backward-compatibly with version field.\n- [ ] Delta artifact emitted comparing old vs new coverage.\n- [ ] G7 gate script updated to handle both v1 and v2 baselines.\n- [ ] All 5 unit test categories pass.\n- [ ] E2E gate runs clean after re-baselining.\n- [ ] No #[ignore] tests, no todo!(), no panics on malformed configs (return Result).\n\n## How this serves the over-arching goals\n\nA regression gate is only as good as its sentinel set. A narrow sentinel set creates the illusion that nothing is regressing while letting wide swaths of the API drift unmonitored. Broadening G7 ensures the \"performance governance\" doctrine in README L932 is actually enforced across the op-family surface, not just the ops that happened to get measured first.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":360,"created_at":"2026-04-09T00:16:30.058406727Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-13T17:36:32.207794236Z","closed_at":"2026-04-13T17:36:32.207615668Z","close_reason":"Extended G7 sentinels: added 12 new workloads covering ufunc-elementwise contiguous (3), broadcast mul (1), FFT expansion (2), strided reductions (1), linalg solve/svd (2), random normal/poisson (2), text-io genfromtxt (1). Updated schema_version to 2.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["performance","phase3"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"franken_numpy-jv28","depends_on_id":"franken_numpy-azql","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-09T00:16:30.058406727Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
